BT 0.1 g /F2 14 Tf 72 560 Td (A STORY ABOUT MONEY) Tj ET
q 0.3 G 1 w 72 555 m 300 555 l S Q
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 530 Td (Maya looked at the shiny toy in the store window. It cost $25. 'I wish) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 510 Td (I had money,' Maya said. Then grandma explained that money is) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 490 Td (something we earn and use carefully. Maya decided to learn everything) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 470 Td (about money - and that's when the adventure began!) Tj ET
BT 0.1 g /F2 14 Tf 72 430 Td (THE LESSON) Tj ET
q 0.3 G 1 w 72 425 m 200 425 l S Q
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 400 Td (Long ago, people used to trade things directly. A farmer might trade eggs) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 380 Td (for bread. But what if the baker didn't want eggs? That was a big problem!) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 360 Td (So people invented money as a way to make trading easier. First, they used) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 340 Td (shells and beads. Then they used metal coins. Today, we use paper bills,) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 320 Td (coins, and even digital money on computers.) Tj ET

