BT 0 g /F2 22 Tf 232.07999999999998 660 Td (Needs vs Wants) Tj ET
BT 0.3 g /F4 12 Tf 41.04000000000002 625 Td (Understanding the difference between needs and wants is the first step to being money smart.) Tj ET
BT 0.1 g /F2 14 Tf 72 560 Td (A STORY ABOUT MONEY) Tj ET
q 0.3 G 1 w 72 555 m 300 555 l S Q
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 530 Td (Jordan really wanted a new video game \($40\) AND new shoes for school) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 510 Td (\($35\). But Jordan only had $50 saved up. 'I can't get both,' Jordan) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 490 Td (realized. That's when Dad said, 'Which one do you NEED and which do) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 470 Td (you WANT?' This question changed everything.) Tj ET
BT 0.1 g /F2 14 Tf 72 430 Td (THE LESSON) Tj ET
q 0.3 G 1 w 72 425 m 200 425 l S Q
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 400 Td (A need is something you must have to survive and be healthy: food, water,) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 380 Td (shelter, clothing, and medicine. A want is something nice to have but you) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 360 Td (can live without: video games, candy, toys, and fancy clothes. Sometimes) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 340 Td (it's tricky to tell the difference! Is a phone a need or a want? It depends) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 320 Td (on the situation.) Tj ET

