BT 0 g /F2 22 Tf 216.24 660 Td (Saving Strategies) Tj ET
BT 0.3 g /F4 12 Tf 55.44 625 Td (Saving money means keeping some of your money for later instead of spending it all now.) Tj ET
BT 0.1 g /F2 14 Tf 72 560 Td (A STORY ABOUT MONEY) Tj ET
q 0.3 G 1 w 72 555 m 300 555 l S Q
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 530 Td (Every time Kai got money, it seemed to disappear! Birthday money -) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 510 Td (gone. Allowance - spent by Tuesday. Then Kai's aunt taught the 3-jar) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 490 Td (system. 'Put money in SAVE, SPEND, and GIVE jars before you do) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 470 Td (anything else.' Three months later, Kai had saved $60!) Tj ET
BT 0.1 g /F2 14 Tf 72 430 Td (THE LESSON) Tj ET
q 0.3 G 1 w 72 425 m 200 425 l S Q
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 400 Td (The best savers follow a simple rule: Pay yourself first! That means before) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 380 Td (you spend any money, put some into savings. Even saving a small amount adds) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 360 Td (up over time. If you save just one dollar a day, you'll have 365 dollars in) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 340 Td (a year! Try the 50-30-20 rule: 50% for needs, 30% for wants, and 20% for) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 320 Td (savings.) Tj ET

endstream
